## Section Construction Spec

### 1. Name Block

```text
FULL NAME
Professional Title / Positioning Line
City, Country · Phone · Email · LinkedIn · Website
```

Rules:

* Name is the largest element on the page.
* Title sits directly below the name.
* Contact line reads as compact metadata, not body copy.
* All three lines align to the same left edge.

### 2. Divider Rule

```text
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
```

Rules:

* Use a single thin line only.
* Place it below the header, not above it.
* Keep spacing above and below consistent.

### 3. Professional Summary

```text
PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
Short paragraph of 3-5 lines with concise executive positioning.
```

Rules:

* Keep it one compact paragraph.
* Do not narrow the paragraph unnecessarily.
* Avoid first-person language and empty claims.

### 4. Core Competencies

Preferred option:

```text
CORE COMPETENCIES
Business Development · Commercial Strategy · Stakeholder Management · Negotiation
Client Relationship Management · Process Improvement · Forecasting · CRM Management
Cross-functional Leadership · Market Analysis
```

Alternate option:

```text
CORE COMPETENCIES
Business Development                  Stakeholder Management
Commercial Strategy                  Contract Negotiation
Pipeline Management                  Market Analysis
Process Improvement                  Client Relationship Management
```

Rules:

* Keep it airy and compact.
* No icons, bullets, progress bars, or ratings.
* Keep all items role-relevant.

### 5. Professional Experience

```text
ROLE TITLE                                                            MMM YYYY - MMM YYYY
Company Name, Location
Optional company descriptor if context is needed
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
```

Rules:

* Role title and date share the same line.
* Date stays flush right across every role.
* Company line sits below the role title.
* Bullets use a consistent hanging indent.
* Space between roles is larger than space between bullets.

### 6. Education

```text
EDUCATION
Degree / Qualification                                                 YYYY - YYYY
Institution, Location
Optional honors / GPA / notable module if relevant
```

Rules:

* Keep entries concise.
* Use the same date alignment logic as experience.
* Sort newest first.

### 7. Certifications

```text
CERTIFICATIONS
Certification Name - Issuer - Year
Certification Name - Issuer - Year
```

Rules:

* Use plain text lines.
* Do not over-design this section.

### 8. Languages

```text
LANGUAGES
English - Native | German - Professional Working Proficiency | Swedish - Conversational
```

Rules:

* Keep it on one line if possible, otherwise wrap cleanly.
* No flags, dots, stars, or icons.

### 9. Technical Skills

```text
TECHNICAL SKILLS
Salesforce · HubSpot · Excel · Power BI · Microsoft 365 · Google Workspace
```

Rules:

* Prefer grouped keywords.
* Avoid dense comma-only lists if readability suffers.

### 10. Additional Information

```text
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
Award Name - Year
Professional Membership - Status
Volunteer Position - Organization
```

Rules:

* Include only if the content adds clear value.
* This section should not visually dominate the page.

## Spacing And Alignment

Vertical rhythm:

```text
[Top margin]
Header content
small gap
Header divider rule
medium gap
Section heading
small gap
Section content
medium gap
...
[Bottom margin]
```

Suggested spacing:

* 4-8 pt between section heading and section content
* 12-16 pt between summary and competencies
* 12-16 pt between competencies and experience
* 10-14 pt between experience entries
* 2-4 pt between bullets inside a role

Alignment system:

```text
LEFT EDGE OF NAME
LEFT EDGE OF TITLE
LEFT EDGE OF CONTACT LINE
LEFT EDGE OF ALL SECTION HEADINGS
LEFT EDGE OF BODY CONTENT
RIGHT EDGE OF DATE COLUMN
RIGHT EDGE OF PAGE CONTENT FIELD
```

Rules:

* Dates must align consistently.
* Do not center body content.
* Do not introduce arbitrary indentation shifts between sections.

## Two-Page Extension Logic

If the CV flows to page 2, keep this structure:

* Page 1: header, summary, competencies, most recent and most important experience entries
* Page 2: remaining experience, education, certifications, languages, technical skills, additional information

Continuation concept:

```text
PAGE 1 ENDS AFTER A COMPLETE ROLE BLOCK IF POSSIBLE

PAGE 2 START
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE (continued only if necessary)                                        │
│ ROLE TITLE                                                            MMM YYYY - MMM YYYY    │
│ Company Name, Location                                                                        │
│ • Bullet                                                                                     │
│ • Bullet                                                                                     │
│                                                                                              │
│ EDUCATION                                                                                    │
│ ...                                                                                          │
│                                                                                              │
│ CERTIFICATIONS                                                                               │
│ ...                                                                                          │
│                                                                                              │
│ LANGUAGES                                                                                    │
│ ...                                                                                          │
│                                                                                              │
│ TECHNICAL SKILLS                                                                             │
│ ...                                                                                          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Rules:

* Do not split a heading from its content at a page break.
* Do not leave a single orphan bullet on page 2 if it can be avoided.
* An optional small repeated name + contact header on page 2 is acceptable only if needed.

## Micro-Detail Checklist

* No photo appears anywhere in the template.
* Name remains the most visually dominant element.
* Title remains secondary to name.
* Contact line is compact and readable.
* Header remains left aligned rather than centered.
* Section headings stay consistent in size, weight, case, and color.
* Summary reads as one compact paragraph.
* Competencies are concise and easy to scan.
* Date column is visually consistent.
* Company/location lines are secondary to role titles.
* Older roles contain fewer bullets than the current role.
* No sidebars, rating bars, colored boxes, decorative shapes, or centered body text.
